<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-2137] Rendering of Type3 string fails with NPE</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2137</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Rendering of the attached PDF fails with a NPE in PDFStreamEngine at the line 395 (float spaceWidthDisp = ...) because the textMatrix field is null. The reason is that the textMatrix gets reset while processing the first character of the string in PageDrawer#drawType3String(). The attached patch fixes the problem, but I am not quite sure whether it is the right solution.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To debug this, set a breakpoint in PDFStreamEngine#processEncodedText() with the condition &quot;string.length == 2 &amp;amp;&amp;amp; string&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; == 67&quot; and watch the textMatrix field vanish after the first character has been processed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
